  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  🎓 VIM LEARNING PATH
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  STAGE 1 – MOVEMENT (you are here ✅):
    hjkl, H/L, J/K, w/b/e, {/}, gg/G, f<char>, sneak (s)

  STAGE 2 – TEXT OBJECTS (learn these next):
    ciw, ci", ci(, daw, diw, yi"
    Rule: think operation first, not where to move

  STAGE 3 – OPERATORS + COUNTS:
    3yy, 5dd, d3w, c2w
    Rule: number + verb + motion = precise editing

  STAGE 4 – MARKS & JUMPS:
    ma, `a, `` (toggle last position)
    gi (jump back to last insert point)

  STAGE 5 – MACROS:
    qa → record, q → stop, @a → replay
    Use for repetitive multi-step edits

  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  ⚡ SPEED TIPS
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  FASTEST FILE NAVIGATION:
    Space+p → Type few letters → Enter (< 2 seconds to any file)

  FASTEST WORD EDIT:
    ciw → type new word (no need to move to start of word first)

  FASTEST STRING EDIT:
    ci" or ci' (cursor anywhere inside the string)

  FASTEST REFACTORING:
    Space+R on variable → Rename everywhere in project

  FASTEST FORMATTING:
    Just save! (Cmd+S or Space+w) → Auto-formats on save

  FASTEST MULTI-EDIT:
    gb → add cursor on next occurrence → keep pressing → edit all at once

  FASTEST COMMENT TOGGLE:
    gc (visual mode) → toggle comment on selected lines

  FASTEST HOVER INFO:
    gh → show type info / docs without leaving keyboard

